Im going vegan…

(Only eating cows that are vegan or identify as tomatoes)

But real talk…

A grass fed carnivore diet is the real vegan diet…

It’s better for you, better for the environment AND even better for animals. 

Vegans will say eating animals is cruel, but then kill 4 billion bees to make almond milk.

Instead of the barbaric diet people assume the carnivore diet is, it actually kills far fewer animals than going vegan.

7.3 billion animals are killed each year for PLANT BASED agriculture.

tilling the soil, cutting down trees and spraying pesticides kills billions of rodents, birds, insects & bees.

Whereas only 40 million cattle are killed a year for beef. 

1 cow produces over 550 lbs of beef, 30 lbs of organs and 100 lbs of fat

That is over 1 million extremely nutritious calories.

Assuming an American eats 2000 calories a day, just 1 cow can feed 1 person for 500 days.

Holy cow is an expression for a reason.

Eat meat. Revere the cow for the incredible creature it is. And go vegan.

Argentinian artist @LeandroErlichOfficial created an illusory swimming pool that appears to be filled with water. Installed as a permanent exhibit at the Museum Voorlinden in the #Netherlands, the pool’s water is actually only 10cm shallow, supported by a thick layer of transparent glass. Below, there lies an aqua room that viewers can enter, inviting a shared experience of wonder at the constructed space from both above and below. In his work, Erlich plays with perception and assumption, exploring the ways we understand phenomena, enter into relationships with spaces, and grasp reality. 🎥: @buzzbinge101 #architectanddesign

🎮 Osteoarthritis is the most common joint pathology seen worldwide and is the leading cause of disability in the US. Even though the exact cause is still unclear, numerous contributing factors have been identified. The common final pathway is characterized by progressive cartilage damage and breakdown. This leads to cartilage failure causing joint pain, loss of joint function and eventually deformity. Patients commonly present with multiple joint involvements, with the knee being affected in 6% of the adult population. 
.
🕹️ Diagnosis of #osteoarthritis of the knee is based on clinical and radiological findings. No universally accepted guidelines or diagnostic criteria h exists. The typical clinical features of #KneeOsteoarthritis include knee pain, decreased range of motion, crepitations, bony tenderness, knee bony enlargement and instability. #Kneepain is the most common symptom, and its cause is multifactorial, with both nociceptive as well as neuropathic mechanisms contributing towards it. The cartilage damage, subchondral bone pathology, periosteum, synovium as well as soft tissue have all been thought to contribute to the pain.
.
Grading the clinical severity of #KneeArthritis needs to consider multiple factors. Acute pain can be graded using visual analogue or numeric scores. But chronic pain and functional impairment require a more comprehensive grading system. The Knee Society Score (KSS) and Western Ontario and McMaster Osteoarthritis Index (WOMAC) provide a holistic understanding of the impact and severity of the OA in the knee. #kneedoctor #kneexray

Struggling with your golf swing?  Payne Stewart’s Weight Transfer Hack is the missing piece you NEED! 

Follow these simple steps and watch your power and accuracy SOAR!

✅Feel the Weight Shift: Start with your weight on your right side (assuming you’re right-handed).
✅Arm Movement Pulls Weight: Imagine your left arm pulling your weight over to your left side as you swing.
✅Find Your Backswing Position: Extend your left arm straight out and turn your left shoulder under your chin. This is your backswing position.
✅Bend and Hit: Now bend at the waist - you’re already in the perfect position to hit the ball!
✅Step Towards Target: Take a small step towards your target with your right foot for added power.

@try_pod traveled to Japan 🇯🇵 and found this unique snake whiskey 🥃 known as Habushu whiskey or snake 🐍 wine. This beverage, a fundamental aspect of Okinawan tradition, originates from Okinawa, Japan. With a history stretching back to the 14th century among the nobility, it is distinguished by its inclusion of pit viper snake venom, a species indigenous to Southeast Asia. The venom plays a crucial role in the drink’s composition and has been identified to contain components that enhance energy, offering an added health benefit that is undeniably advantageous.

media.caption:
Hey friend ,

I want to share a little thought with you today. 

Life’s full of moments, some planned, some totally unexpected. 

And sometimes, it’s the unexpected ones, even the mistakes, that bring us the most joy. 

Like this funny little story: Imagine asking your spouse to pick up an energy-saving light bulb, but instead, they come home with a sound-activated one. 

Now, picture being a chef, in the middle of the kitchen chaos, and every loud noise turns the light off. 

The only way to turn it back on? 

A loud, hearty “aroooo!” It’s a scene straight out of a comedy show!

Sure, this light bulb might not make it past a day in your house before getting swapped out for the right one. 

But think about the laughter, the teasing, and the love that fills the air because of this silly mistake. 

Those memories? 

They’re going to stick around a lot longer than any light bulb ever could.

So, let’s make a little more room for laughter in our lives. 

Let’s cherish the harmless mistakes, the mix-ups that leave us shaking our heads one minute and bursting into laughter the next. 

Because it’s these moments, these memories, that weave the rich tapestry of our lives together.

Remember, it’s not about being perfect. 

It’s about enjoying the ride, missteps and all, and finding joy in the journey.

Take care,

- Mindset Mastery Crew

P.S. Next time something goes a bit sideways, instead of getting frustrated, try finding the humor in it. You might just end up with a great story to tell.

AI, despite its rapid advancement, is unlikely to fully replace humans due to several intrinsic limitations. First, AI lacks the depth of human creativity and emotional intelligence, crucial for innovation and understanding complex human emotions.

Secondly, ethical and moral decision-making, inherently human traits, cannot be authentically programmed into AI, which operates on algorithms and data. Furthermore, AI depends on humans for design, programming, and continuous improvement, indicating a collaborative rather than a replacement relationship.

The nuanced understanding and adaptability humans possess in changing contexts and unforeseen situations remain unmatched by AI.

This symbiotic relationship underscores the enhancement rather than replacement, with AI augmenting human capabilities, not fully taking over the roles that require emotional depth, ethical judgments, and creative insights.

✩ MercuryMercury is the closest planet from the Sun. The side facing the sun is extremely hot, whereas the other side is incredibly cold. The temperatures range from -150 C to 425. Without your spacesuit, you’d either freeze or instantly turn into a carbon brick, depending on which side of the planet you were standing on.Without any gear, you would survive for less than 2 minutes.✩VenusIt is a real hell.The temperature on its surface is approximately 400 C. Its surface pressure is also about 90 times greater than that of Earth. A spacesuit designed for Venus would need to be constructed of titanium. Without a spacesuit, one would get squashed in seconds, if you didn’t get turned into dust.✩Earth:Thanks to the wonderful atmosphere, food and water, and everything else that makes our home planet liveable, you can get in a good 80 or more years here. Earth is perfect for us.✩MarsIt is very cold, but the atmosphere is very thin ‘Tyson says, “so the intensity of the cold won’t be as biting as it might otherwise feel at that temperature on Earth.”✩ JupiterJupiter is literally just a ball of gas with a solid core. So there’s nothing to land on. If you were to jump on it, you would just descend into nothingness. The gases inside this giant are highly pressurized, so without any gear, you would get crushed instantly, i.e., in less than 1 second.✰✰✰ Just like Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune are enormous balls of gas. One would get crushed almost instantly if you attempted to stand on these planets in any condition.

A crosswalk at the entrance to Granville Island in Vancouver has a new feature to help pedestrians cross safely — and it’s not what you’d expect. 

On either side of the crosswalk, pedestrians are invited to take a red foam brick that they can wave while crossing, to grab the attention of drivers.

“It’s super effective once [drivers] see you’re holding a brick — like, oh yeah, I better stop and let this person go. So it gives the power back, kind of, to the pedestrian.”

There are numerous disabilities around the world. Some are visible, like using a wheelchair and some are invisible like ADHD. Sometimes, people like me talk slower than the average person due to the disability I have. That doesn't stop me from living life. I simply share my story to spread awareness and to break the stigma about people with disabilities.

How to cook Alligator 🐊
Recipe below ⤵️

This was a 31 pound Alligator 🐊 to give you a better gauge on the cost/temps/times of this entire cook!

🐊 Brine overnight with lemons, Oranges, Apples, Brown Sugar, Salt, Cinnamon, and Thyme. 
🐊 I used @bearandburtons W Sauce as a binder 
🐊 Then use your favorite BBQ Rub
🐊 Using @thermopro Twin TempSpike I stuck the probes in the thickest part of the tail. 
🐊 In the smoker at 275 degrees spritzing with every 30 minutes with 50/50 Apple Juice and Worcestershire Sauce. 
🐊 When the Internal Temperature reached 165 degrees I painted on BBQ sauce and let it tack on for 30 minutes. 
🐊 This cook took roughly 6 hours and I let the Alligator rest for 30 minutes!

Do you know that it is not just a kernel, but a part of a larger system called GNU/Linux? As Richard Stallman, the founder of the GNU Project, said: “There is no system but GNU and Linux is one of it’s kernels.”
GNU is an operating system that aims to be a free replacement for UNIX, with a collection of software programs and development tools. Linux is a kernel that manages the hardware resources and communicates with the devices. Together, they form the GNU/Linux system, which is widely used by millions of users around the world.
Linux is a complex example of the wisdom of crowds, as it is developed by thousands of volunteers who contribute code, bug fixes, documentation, and support. It is also a testament to the power of open source, as anyone can access, modify, and distribute the source code under the GNU General Public License.

The concept of connecting black holes, wormholes, and white holes is purely theoretical and speculative at this point, but the idea revolves around the interconnectedness of spacetime and the potential for exotic structures within it.

Here's a speculative scenario that some theories propose:

1. BLACKHOLE FORMATION - A black hole forms when a massive star collapses under its own gravity at the end of its life cycle. This collapse creates a region of spacetime with such a strong gravitational pull that nothing, not even light, can escape from it.

2. WORMHOLE CONNECTION - Within the event horizon of the black hole, some theoretical models suggest the possibility of a wormhole—a tunnel through spacetime that could connect the black hole to another region of spacetime. This wormhole could potentially extend beyond the event horizon and connect to a distant region, possibly to a white hole.

3. WHITE HOLE - On the other end of the hypothetical wormhole could exist a white hole. Unlike black holes, which draw matter and energy into them, white holes are theorized to expel matter and energy outward. This could create a region of spacetime where matter and energy emerge, possibly in a different location and time, essentially acting as the counterpart to a black hole.

4. CONNECTION - In this speculative scenario, the black hole, wormhole, and white hole are interconnected through the fabric of spacetime. Matter and energy falling into the black hole could potentially emerge from the white hole through the wormhole connection.

It's important to emphasize that this scenario is highly speculative and not supported by observational evidence. The existence of wormholes, black holes, and white holes remains theoretical, and the idea of connecting them in this manner is even more speculative. It's an intriguing concept that arises from attempts to reconcile general relativity with quantum mechanics, but it's currently beyond the realm of established science.

Blast from the past, 2007: The Vintage 1945 Girard Perregaux Tourbillon Jackpot in rose gold stands out as one of the most extraordinary Girard-Perregaux wristwatches ever created. 🕰✨ The Caliber GPFAY08 of this watch is a homage to Charles Fey’s ‘Liberty Bell’ slot machine (designed in 1898), crafted in collaboration with Christophe Claret.

This timepiece features a tourbillon with a golden bridge of characteristic baroque design, registered by Girard-Perregaux as early as 1884, and boasts a chiming slot machine mechanism. 🎰🎶 Its three rollers, visible at the top of the dial, display five symbols: a heart, diamond, spade, horseshoe, and the liberty bell for the jackpot. 🎉 When the arm on the right side of the case is pulled, the slot machine mechanism is activated, simultaneously triggering another mechanism that chimes on the gong as each of the rollers stops.

Audi Matrix LED technology is an advanced lighting system that uses a matrix of individual LEDs (Light Emitting Diodes) to dynamically control the distribution and intensity of light on the road. 

It works by dividing the headlights into multiple segments, each controlled individually by sensors and algorithms. This allows for precise adjustment of the light pattern to optimize visibility without dazzling other road users.

 The system can detect other vehicles and adjust the beam pattern accordingly, providing maximum illumination while minimizing glare for oncoming traffic.

The mouse, in its quiet little world, found itself startled, flabbergasted even, by a sound that tore through the silence like a clap of thunder in a clear sky 🌩️. It was a sound so unexpected, so utterly alien to its delicate ears 🐭👂, accustomed only to the gentle whispers of the wind 🌬️, the soft murmur of the earth 🌍, and the rhythmic heartbeats of its own tiny chest ❤️. Imagine, if you will, this tiny creature, its heart a fluttering drum, its eyes wide as saucers 👀, frozen in a moment where time seemed to stretch into infinity ⏳.

This sound, what was it? To us, perhaps a mere dropping of a book 📚, a slamming of a door 🚪, or the distant rumble of traffic 🚗. But to this tiny being, it was a cataclysm, an upheaval of its entire universe 🌌. It's in these moments, these minute, seemingly insignificant events, that we find a mirror to our own experiences. Haven't we all been that mouse at some point? Haven't we all faced moments that, although possibly mundane to others, shook our core and made us reassess our place in the world 🌎?

This story, this tiny narrative of a mouse and a sound, is a testament to the universality of feeling small, of feeling overwhelmed by the vast and unpredictable nature of existence. Yet, it's also a reminder of resilience 💪, of the remarkable ability to recover, to adapt, and to continue, despite the odds. The mouse, after its initial shock, will go on. It will return to its foraging, to its life, carrying with it the memory of the sound, but also the knowledge that it can, and will, endure 🌟.

So, next time you find yourself flabbergasted by the loud sounds of life 📢, the unexpected challenges, or the seemingly insurmountable obstacles, remember the mouse 🐁. Remember that fear, surprise, and uncertainty are universal, but so are strength, resilience, and the capacity to move forward. Let's embrace our moments of being flabbergasted, not with fear, but with the understanding that they are simply part of our journey 🛤️, teaching us, shaping us, and making us stronger 💖.

What is Situational Awareness?

Situational awareness involves possessing a precise comprehension of the ongoing situation or system relevant to oneself, whether engaged in flying, monitoring or controlling aircraft, attending to passengers, or maintaining aircraft or systems. 

Operationally, situational awareness necessitates maintaining a sufficient understanding of the present and evolving state of a situation or system, enabling anticipation of future variations or developments in the system or environment.

Normal calculator evaluates an expression in the same order in which inputs are given.
But mobile calculator evaluates an expression according to BODMAS rule. You can find correct answer of any expression using BODMAS rule. Or we can say that answer got from BODMAS rule is the only correct answer you can get.

According to BODMAS rule, the brackets have to be solved first followed by powers or roots (i.e. of), then Division, Multiplication, Addition, and at the end Subtraction. Solving any expression is considered correct only if the BODMAS rule or the PEDMAS rule is followed to solve it.

Im going vegan…

(Only eating cows that are vegan or identify as tomatoes)

But real talk…

A grass fed carnivore diet is the real vegan diet…

It’s better for you, better for the environment AND even better for animals. 

Vegans will say eating animals is cruel, but then kill 4 billion bees to make almond milk.

Instead of the barbaric diet people assume the carnivore diet is, it actually kills far fewer animals than going vegan.

7.3 billion animals are killed each year for PLANT BASED agriculture.

tilling the soil, cutting down trees and spraying pesticides kills billions of rodents, birds, insects & bees.

Whereas only 40 million cattle are killed a year for beef. 

1 cow produces over 550 lbs of beef, 30 lbs of organs and 100 lbs of fat

That is over 1 million extremely nutritious calories.

Assuming an American eats 2000 calories a day, just 1 cow can feed 1 person for 500 days.

Holy cow is an expression for a reason.

Eat meat. Revere the cow for the incredible creature it is. And go vegan.

Argentinian artist @LeandroErlichOfficial created an illusory swimming pool that appears to be filled with water. Installed as a permanent exhibit at the Museum Voorlinden in the #Netherlands, the pool’s water is actually only 10cm shallow, supported by a thick layer of transparent glass. Below, there lies an aqua room that viewers can enter, inviting a shared experience of wonder at the constructed space from both above and below. In his work, Erlich plays with perception and assumption, exploring the ways we understand phenomena, enter into relationships with spaces, and grasp reality. 🎥: @buzzbinge101 #architectanddesign

🎮 Osteoarthritis is the most common joint pathology seen worldwide and is the leading cause of disability in the US. Even though the exact cause is still unclear, numerous contributing factors have been identified. The common final pathway is characterized by progressive cartilage damage and breakdown. This leads to cartilage failure causing joint pain, loss of joint function and eventually deformity. Patients commonly present with multiple joint involvements, with the knee being affected in 6% of the adult population. 
.
🕹️ Diagnosis of #osteoarthritis of the knee is based on clinical and radiological findings. No universally accepted guidelines or diagnostic criteria h exists. The typical clinical features of #KneeOsteoarthritis include knee pain, decreased range of motion, crepitations, bony tenderness, knee bony enlargement and instability. #Kneepain is the most common symptom, and its cause is multifactorial, with both nociceptive as well as neuropathic mechanisms contributing towards it. The cartilage damage, subchondral bone pathology, periosteum, synovium as well as soft tissue have all been thought to contribute to the pain.
.
Grading the clinical severity of #KneeArthritis needs to consider multiple factors. Acute pain can be graded using visual analogue or numeric scores. But chronic pain and functional impairment require a more comprehensive grading system. The Knee Society Score (KSS) and Western Ontario and McMaster Osteoarthritis Index (WOMAC) provide a holistic understanding of the impact and severity of the OA in the knee. #kneedoctor #kneexray

Struggling with your golf swing?  Payne Stewart’s Weight Transfer Hack is the missing piece you NEED! 

Follow these simple steps and watch your power and accuracy SOAR!

✅Feel the Weight Shift: Start with your weight on your right side (assuming you’re right-handed).
✅Arm Movement Pulls Weight: Imagine your left arm pulling your weight over to your left side as you swing.
✅Find Your Backswing Position: Extend your left arm straight out and turn your left shoulder under your chin. This is your backswing position.
✅Bend and Hit: Now bend at the waist - you’re already in the perfect position to hit the ball!
✅Step Towards Target: Take a small step towards your target with your right foot for added power.

This beverage, a fundamental aspect of Okinawan tradition, originates from Okinawa, Japan. With a history stretching back to the 14th century among the nobility, it is distinguished by its inclusion of pit viper snake venom, a species indigenous to Southeast Asia. The venom plays a crucial role in the drink’s composition and has been identified to contain components that enhance energy, offering an added health benefit that is undeniably advantageous.

media.caption:
Hey friend ,

I want to share a little thought with you today. 

Life’s full of moments, some planned, some totally unexpected. 

And sometimes, it’s the unexpected ones, even the mistakes, that bring us the most joy. 

Like this funny little story: Imagine asking your spouse to pick up an energy-saving light bulb, but instead, they come home with a sound-activated one. 

Now, picture being a chef, in the middle of the kitchen chaos, and every loud noise turns the light off. 

The only way to turn it back on? 

A loud, hearty “aroooo!” It’s a scene straight out of a comedy show!

Sure, this light bulb might not make it past a day in your house before getting swapped out for the right one. 

But think about the laughter, the teasing, and the love that fills the air because of this silly mistake. 

Those memories? 

They’re going to stick around a lot longer than any light bulb ever could.

So, let’s make a little more room for laughter in our lives. 

Let’s cherish the harmless mistakes, the mix-ups that leave us shaking our heads one minute and bursting into laughter the next. 

Because it’s these moments, these memories, that weave the rich tapestry of our lives together.

Remember, it’s not about being perfect. 

It’s about enjoying the ride, missteps and all, and finding joy in the journey.

Take care,

- Mindset Mastery Crew

P.S. Next time something goes a bit sideways, instead of getting frustrated, try finding the humor in it. You might just end up with a great story to tell.

AI, despite its rapid advancement, is unlikely to fully replace humans due to several intrinsic limitations. First, AI lacks the depth of human creativity and emotional intelligence, crucial for innovation and understanding complex human emotions.

Secondly, ethical and moral decision-making, inherently human traits, cannot be authentically programmed into AI, which operates on algorithms and data. Furthermore, AI depends on humans for design, programming, and continuous improvement, indicating a collaborative rather than a replacement relationship.

The nuanced understanding and adaptability humans possess in changing contexts and unforeseen situations remain unmatched by AI.

This symbiotic relationship underscores the enhancement rather than replacement, with AI augmenting human capabilities, not fully taking over the roles that require emotional depth, ethical judgments, and creative insights.

✩ MercuryMercury is the closest planet from the Sun. The side facing the sun is extremely hot, whereas the other side is incredibly cold. The temperatures range from -150 C to 425. Without your spacesuit, you’d either freeze or instantly turn into a carbon brick, depending on which side of the planet you were standing on.Without any gear, you would survive for less than 2 minutes.✩VenusIt is a real hell.The temperature on its surface is approximately 400 C. Its surface pressure is also about 90 times greater than that of Earth. A spacesuit designed for Venus would need to be constructed of titanium. Without a spacesuit, one would get squashed in seconds, if you didn’t get turned into dust.✩Earth:Thanks to the wonderful atmosphere, food and water, and everything else that makes our home planet liveable, you can get in a good 80 or more years here. Earth is perfect for us.✩MarsIt is very cold, but the atmosphere is very thin ‘Tyson says, “so the intensity of the cold won’t be as biting as it might otherwise feel at that temperature on Earth.”✩ JupiterJupiter is literally just a ball of gas with a solid core. So there’s nothing to land on. If you were to jump on it, you would just descend into nothingness. The gases inside this giant are highly pressurized, so without any gear, you would get crushed instantly, i.e., in less than 1 second.✰✰✰ Just like Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune are enormous balls of gas. A crosswalk at the entrance to Granville Island in Vancouver has a new feature to help pedestrians cross safely — and it’s not what you’d expect. 

On either side of the crosswalk, pedestrians are invited to take a red foam brick that they can wave while crossing, to grab the attention of drivers.

“It’s super effective once [drivers] see you’re holding a brick — like, oh yeah, I better stop and let this person go. So it gives the power back, kind of, to the pedestrian.”

There are numerous disabilities around the world. Some are visible, like using a wheelchair and some are invisible like ADHD. Sometimes, people like me talk slower than the average person due to the disability I have. That doesn't stop me from living life. I simply share my story to spread awareness and to break the stigma about people with disabilities.

Do you know that it is not just a kernel, but a part of a larger system called GNU/Linux? As Richard Stallman, the founder of the GNU Project, said: “There is no system but GNU and Linux is one of it’s kernels.”
GNU is an operating system that aims to be a free replacement for UNIX, with a collection of software programs and development tools. Linux is a kernel that manages the hardware resources and communicates with the devices. Together, they form the GNU/Linux system, which is widely used by millions of users around the world.
Linux is a complex example of the wisdom of crowds, as it is developed by thousands of volunteers who contribute code, bug fixes, documentation, and support. It is also a testament to the power of open source, as anyone can access, modify, and distribute the source code under the GNU General Public License.

The concept of connecting black holes, wormholes, and white holes is purely theoretical and speculative at this point, but the idea revolves around the interconnectedness of spacetime and the potential for exotic structures within it.

Here's a speculative scenario that some theories propose:

1. BLACKHOLE FORMATION - A black hole forms when a massive star collapses under its own gravity at the end of its life cycle. This collapse creates a region of spacetime with such a strong gravitational pull that nothing, not even light, can escape from it.

2. WORMHOLE CONNECTION - Within the event horizon of the black hole, some theoretical models suggest the possibility of a wormhole—a tunnel through spacetime that could connect the black hole to another region of spacetime. This wormhole could potentially extend beyond the event horizon and connect to a distant region, possibly to a white hole.

3. WHITE HOLE - On the other end of the hypothetical wormhole could exist a white hole. Unlike black holes, which draw matter and energy into them, white holes are theorized to expel matter and energy outward. This could create a region of spacetime where matter and energy emerge, possibly in a different location and time, essentially acting as the counterpart to a black hole.

4. CONNECTION - In this speculative scenario, the black hole, wormhole, and white hole are interconnected through the fabric of spacetime. Matter and energy falling into the black hole could potentially emerge from the white hole through the wormhole connection.

It's important to emphasize that this scenario is highly speculative and not supported by observational evidence. The existence of wormholes, black holes, and white holes remains theoretical, and the idea of connecting them in this manner is even more speculative. It's an intriguing concept that arises from attempts to reconcile general relativity with quantum mechanics, but it's currently beyond the realm of established science.

Blast from the past, 2007: The Vintage 1945 Girard Perregaux Tourbillon Jackpot in rose gold stands out as one of the most extraordinary Girard-Perregaux wristwatches ever created. 🕰✨ The Caliber GPFAY08 of this watch is a homage to Charles Fey’s ‘Liberty Bell’ slot machine (designed in 1898), crafted in collaboration with Christophe Claret.

This timepiece features a tourbillon with a golden bridge of characteristic baroque design, registered by Girard-Perregaux as early as 1884, and boasts a chiming slot machine mechanism. 🎰🎶 Its three rollers, visible at the top of the dial, display five symbols: a heart, diamond, spade, horseshoe, and the liberty bell for the jackpot. 🎉 When the arm on the right side of the case is pulled, the slot machine mechanism is activated, simultaneously triggering another mechanism that chimes on the gong as each of the rollers stops.

The mouse, in its quiet little world, found itself startled, flabbergasted even, by a sound that tore through the silence like a clap of thunder in a clear sky 🌩️. It was a sound so unexpected, so utterly alien to its delicate ears 🐭👂, accustomed only to the gentle whispers of the wind 🌬️, the soft murmur of the earth 🌍, and the rhythmic heartbeats of its own tiny chest ❤️. Imagine, if you will, this tiny creature, its heart a fluttering drum, its eyes wide as saucers 👀, frozen in a moment where time seemed to stretch into infinity ⏳.

This sound, what was it? To us, perhaps a mere dropping of a book 📚, a slamming of a door 🚪, or the distant rumble of traffic 🚗. But to this tiny being, it was a cataclysm, an upheaval of its entire universe 🌌. It's in these moments, these minute, seemingly insignificant events, that we find a mirror to our own experiences. Haven't we all been that mouse at some point? Haven't we all faced moments that, although possibly mundane to others, shook our core and made us reassess our place in the world 🌎?

This story, this tiny narrative of a mouse and a sound, is a testament to the universality of feeling small, of feeling overwhelmed by the vast and unpredictable nature of existence. Yet, it's also a reminder of resilience 💪, of the remarkable ability to recover, to adapt, and to continue, despite the odds. The mouse, after its initial shock, will go on. It will return to its foraging, to its life, carrying with it the memory of the sound, but also the knowledge that it can, and will, endure 🌟.

So, next time you find yourself flabbergasted by the loud sounds of life 📢, the unexpected challenges, or the seemingly insurmountable obstacles, remember the mouse 🐁. Remember that fear, surprise, and uncertainty are universal, but so are strength, resilience, and the capacity to move forward. Let's embrace our moments of being flabbergasted, not with fear, but with the understanding that they are simply part of our journey 🛤️, teaching us, shaping us, and making us stronger 💖.

What is Situational Awareness?

Situational awareness involves possessing a precise comprehension of the ongoing situation or system relevant to oneself, whether engaged in flying, monitoring or controlling aircraft, attending to passengers, or maintaining aircraft or systems. 

Operationally, situational awareness necessitates maintaining a sufficient understanding of the present and evolving state of a situation or system, enabling anticipation of future variations or developments in the system or environment.

Normal calculator evaluates an expression in the same order in which inputs are given.
But mobile calculator evaluates an expression according to BODMAS rule. You can find correct answer of any expression using BODMAS rule. Or we can say that answer got from BODMAS rule is the only correct answer you can get.

According to BODMAS rule, the brackets have to be solved first followed by powers or roots (i.e. of), then Division, Multiplication, Addition, and at the end Subtraction. Solving any expression is considered correct only if the BODMAS rule or the PEDMAS rule is followed to solve it.

The Face of Christ by Claude Mellan, 1649

The remarkable thing about this engraving is that it is created from a single spiraling line of 150 meters long, starting at the tip of Jesus’ nose. The engraving is also known as the Veil of Veronica (or the Sudarium of Saint Veronica), referring to the cloth used by Veronica to wipe the face of Jesus on his way to his crucifixion.

Mellan created it using a burin (a chisel-like tool) to engrave into a copperplate. He changed the angle and pressure of the burin to make the line thicker/thinner and lighter/darker in certain places to create the face.

Grigory Sokolov, age 37 performing Chopin’s Etude Op. 25 No. 12 in C minor (“Ocean”) in 1987. Note that this performance was an encore after he played Brahms’ Piano Concerto No. 2
•
Sokolov’s power and attack here is almost intimidating. The voicing, which is so often muffled, is crystal-clear, and the clarity in each arpeggio is breathtaking. Sokolov was born in St. Petersburg and began studying the piano at the age of five, entering the Leningrad Conservatory’s special school for children at age seven to study with Leah Zelikhman. At age 12, he gave his first major recital and at age 16, won the gold medal at the 1966 International Tchaikovsky Piano Competition, making him the youngest winner to ever do so. Emil Gilels, chairman of the Tchaikovsky Competition jury, subsequently championed Sokolov’s work. Daniil Trifonov has said about him: “Sokolov is a musical figure of intense magnitude. Attending his performances, one may have the sensation of the sound possessing a nearly physical essence; it fills the entire concert hall with rare energy and lives in its own time sphere.”

A dança é uma forma de expressão cultural e artística que pode ser encontrada em todas as sociedades ao redor do mundo. Ela pode ser usada para contar histórias, expressar emoções, celebrar eventos e rituais, ou simplesmente para diversão e exercício físico. Existem inúmeras formas de dança, desde as tradicionais até as contemporâneas, cada uma com suas técnicas, estilos e significados únicos.
A dança é importante por várias razões:

1. Expressão cultural: Ela reflete a identidade e os valores de uma sociedade, preservando tradições e transmitindo histórias ao longo das gerações.

2. Expressão emocional: Permite que os dançarinos expressem uma ampla gama de emoções, desde a alegria até a tristeza, de uma forma física e visceral.

3. Saúde física e mental: A prática regular de dança melhora a condição física, promove a coordenação motora, fortalece os músculos e contribui para o bem-estar emocional e mental.

4. Comunicação não verbal: A dança é uma forma de comunicação não verbal que transcende barreiras linguísticas, permitindo que as pessoas se conectem e se entendam através do movimento e da expressão corporal.

5. Criatividade e autoexpressão: Proporciona uma plataforma para a criatividade e a autoexpressão, permitindo que os dançarinos explorem e desenvolvam sua própria voz artística.

6. Cooperação e trabalho em equipe: Em muitas formas de dança, especialmente em grupos ou em pares, é necessário cooperar e trabalhar em equipe, promovendo habilidades sociais e de colaboração.

Esses são apenas alguns dos motivos pelos quais a dança é considerada uma forma de arte e uma atividade culturalmente significativa em todo o mundo.

Seals often slap their flippers against their bodies, a behavior known as “clapping” or “flipperslapping.” This action serves multiple purposes for seals. It can be a form of communication, used to signal other seals or to express dominance or aggression. Additionally, seals may slap their flippers as a way to maintain body temperature by stimulating blood circulation. Sometimes, this behavior is also observed during play or as a means of catching the attention of nearby seals or humans. Overall, flipperslapping is a fascinating behavior that plays various roles in the social dynamics and physiology of seals.

La domenica di Pasqua a Firenze vuol dire Scoppio del Carro. Si è rinnovata questa mattina l’antica tradizione popolare fiorentina che, da oltre nove secoli, rievoca le gesta dei fiorentini alle Crociate e il loro ritorno in città nel 1101.
Come ogni mattina di Pasqua, il “Carro del Fuoco”, che i fiorentini chiamano Brindellone, accompagnato dal Corteo Storico della Repubblica Fiorentina, è partito dal deposito di Via il Prato per raggiungere Piazza Duomo e posizionarsi davanti alla Cattedrale.
Alle 9.30 è arrivato il Gonfalone, con il Sindaco, le Autorità e il Corteo Storico della Repubblica Fiorentina con il “Carro del Fuoco” in Piazza Duomo.
Alle 11 è arrivato il momento clou della mattinata, quello più atteso: la Colombina che deve accendere il Carro. All’interno della chiesa, l’arcivescovo accende un razzo a forma di colomba che vola fuori dalla chiesa percorrendo un filo che va a colpire il Carro nella piazza, dando vita a spettacolari fuochi d’artificio. Se la Colombina compie l’intero percorso senza intoppi, come vuole la tradizione, significa che l’andamento dell’attività agricola avrà una “buona sorte”. 
 E ieri mattina è andata proprio così: la Colombina ha compiuto un volo perfetto, accendendo il Brindellone e dando il via allo spettacolo pirotecnico.

Easter Sunday in Florence means Scoppio del Carro. Yesterday morning, the ancient Florentine popular tradition was renewed, which, for over nine centuries, has reevoked the deeds of the Florentines at the Crusades and their return to the city in 1101.

The BMW iX Flow concept car is the first color-changing car in the world, and it uses electronic ink (E-ink) technology. The car's body is covered with digital paper that's laser-cut into a triangle mesh, and it contains microcapsules that contain white and black pigments. When an electrical field is sent to the microcapsules, the white or black pigments collect on the surface, changing the color of the car. The car can change from white to black, and the black color can help absorb heat on cold days. 
The E-ink technology is similar to what's used in modern-day electronic books. The material used in the car has different pigments that cause the color to change or create dual-colored patterns. The car's body is made of a material similar to an Amazon Kindle E-Reader, and it's tailored to the car's contours

Reese’s Peanut Butter Cups OR Protein Peanut Butter Cups⁉️

1 reese’s cup = 100 calories 
1 Protein peanut butter cup = 25 calories 

Steal this recipe that packs over 70g of protein and made me 24 peanut butter cups for the same amount of calories as 6 Reese’s peanut butter cups. 

This recipe made so much food that I was satisfied with only 2. I was shocked and these lasted me the entire week. 

Having a sweet tooth is no excuse to stuff your face with garbage. Especially when there are other options like this. 
 When you choose an option that is higher in protein, it will always be more SATIATING (leave you fuller for longer). 

Also because the protein cups are high-volume, that

So even though they are 1/4 the calories, they feel like way more food. 

I’m not saying you can’t have your favorite candy here and there, but when you try this recipe, it might make you think twice. 

✅Macros for the Protein Peanut Butter Cups: (made 24 cups, it may make you less depending on your pan size) 
571 calories 78g protein 41g carbs 13g Fat 

✅Ingredients: 
✅1 cup greek yogurt
✅1 scoop of chocolate protein powder (I used cocoa gains from @alpha.lion use code TRIZZLEMAN for a discount)
✅1 scoop of peanut butter protein powder or PB fit (I used PB & Gains from @alpha.lion use code TRIZZLEMAN for a discount)
✅3 tbsp chocolate chips or sugar free chocolate sauce (for less calories)
✅3 tbsp water

✅Directions

✅First, mix your greek yogurt and chocolate protein into a bowl 
✅ Place the mixture into a non stick rubber muffin pan
✅Mix the peanut butter protein and water in a seperate bowl
✅Apply a thin layer of the peanut butter mixture on each of the cups in the muffin pan
✅Place the pan in the freezer for 2-3 hours
✅After the cups are frozen, Melt chocolate chips (or take sugar free chocolate sauce) and apply a thin layer to each cup 
✅Place back into the freezer for a few minutes
✅ENJOY!

: I declare it the most stunning lookout point in San Francisco Bay Area(Updated). Unlike Hawaii’s strenuous hike to stairways to heaven, it’s just a 650-step stroll from the parking lot! 

Also not only does it offer a breathtaking view of the Pacific Ocean, but also has an equally stunning view of the Golden Gate Bridge! Stay tuned for part 2. 

📍Hawk hill, Marin Headlands, just north of the Golden Gate Bridge. (Updated) 

How to reach Hawk Hill?

The hill is very accessible and easily findable on Google maps. Driving access is by Conzelman Rd. There is a FREE parking just before the road turns into a one-way road going to Point Lomita lighthouse.
You can park there and do less than a mile hike to get to this View point, which is located at the NW side of the parking lot.

Tanghulu in less than 5 mins! 🍓

** FYI, the sugar and the dipping containers get SUPER hot because you’re microwaving this for a few mins. Make sure to use protective gear*! 

Serving size: 1 
 
-4 tbsp sugar
-2 tbsp water
-washed and fully dried fruit of choice

Steps: 
1. Add the sugar into a heat safe vessel and add the water. DONT stir. 
2. Place into a microwave and microwave on 30 second increments until the sugar dissolves and turns an amber color. DO NOT mix or stir the sugar between microwave increments! This disturbs the crystallization 
2.5. If you do larger portions (like the one I tripled) you can microwave for 1 min increments! 

** THE SUGAR BURNS FAST** so once you see that the sugar is dissolved and starts to turn color, go down to 15 second increments until it’s at an amber color. 

Total cook time for 1 serving is about 3-4 mins (6-8 30 second increments) in the microwave. 
3. Dip your fruit in and immediately place into an ice bath. 
Enjoy immediately!

Making a budget for each month (before the month begins) and sticking to it is the key to winning with money.💵
 
Here’s how to create a simple zero-based budget each month👇
 
1. Write down your total income.
 
2. List your expenses (including any money you’ll save).
 
3. Subtract expenses from income to equal zero. This is called a zero-based budget, and it helps you give every dollar you made that month a clear purpose.
 
4. Track your spending to make sure you stick to your plan.

media.caption:
⤵️ 6 ULTIMATE CALIFORNIA TRAVEL DUPES (save for future planning)

Did you know that some of the most incredible destinations in the world have their very own duplicates right here in California? 🤯 

From the Swiss Alps to Mars (yes, you read that right!), I’ve got you covered with these 6 unbelievable California ultimate travel dupes! 

Travel the world without leaving California:

1️⃣ Thousand Island Lake - The stunning duplicate for Switzerland’s picturesque mountains. This reminds me of Five Lakes Trail with the view of Matterhorn.🇨🇭

2️⃣ Trona Pinnacles - an out-of-this-world experience at this Mars landscape lookalike! ☄️

3️⃣ Big Pine Lake - A slice of Italy’s Dolomites right here in SoCal! This lake makes me think of Lago Federa. 🇮🇹

4️⃣ Mesquite Sand Dunes - Feel like you’re in the Sahara Desert without leaving California! 🏜️

5️⃣ Minaret Lake - This hidden gem reminds me of Argentina’s Patagonian peaks! 🇦🇷

6️⃣ Red Rock Canyon - this off the beaten path destination reminds me of Jordan’s otherworldly landscapes! 🏕️

Opinions are my own, but trust me when I say these spots will leave you speechless! 

Which one will be your next California adventure destination??

✨Open Me✨

Here’s the story:

I was doing a sideline interview after a player got a touchdown. 

The play had resumed and I didn’t see that the kick returner was running right at me.

The player did and lifted me up over the other player who basically slid right underneath my feet.

This player (shout out to the U of M’s Bison’s Brendt Adams!!!) had incredible reflexes and saved me from a massive, painful wipe out.

Oh, and we were live on air while this happened. 

When he put me down, I said “He not only scores TD, he also saves lives. Thanks for the interview!” And we both walked away laughing. 

Here is how I remained calm:

- I am very practiced at supportive self-talk when public speaking. I am ready to tell myself that I am ok. That I can manage what is happening. 

- Also, I know that mistakes happen when you’re doing any type of public speaking. So my attitude when something “goes wrong” is that it’s supposed to.

This situation was shocking but it wasn’t embarrassing. That is when you really need to be prepared to be on your side.

I’ve done things like call a player by the wrong name or not realize I’ve got live to air. While you obviously want to minimize these mistakes - beating yourself up in the moment will only make things worse and cause further error!

I teach exactly how to do this in my Deliver Your Best Essentials handbook. 

Comment “Essentials” and I’ll send you the link so you can get started on changing your self-talk and managing mistakes this week!!

Breakfast Tacos!

Salsa
1 red onion, roughly chopped
1 jalapeno
4 roma tomatoes
4 cloves garlic
1/4 cup finely chopped cilantro
juice of one lime
1 tsp cumin
salt to taste

Ingredients
1 lb bacon
5 eggs
corn tortillas
2 Tbsp butter

Method
Preheat oven to 400f
Add your tomatoes, onion, jalapeno, garlic to a large pan and cook over high heat until lightly charred. Using a molcajete or blender, smash or blend all of your charred vegetables. Once a salsa forms, add your cilantro, cumin, salt and lime juice. Mix well and set aside. 
Lay your bacon out on a sheet tray. Add to your preheated oven and cook for about 25 minutes or until crispy. Next, chop your bacon and set aside.

In a bowl, add your eggs and season with salt and pepper. Mix until smooth. Heat a non stick over medium heat. Add your butter and once melted, add your eggs. Stir constantly with a silicone spatula and cook until your liking. Then, set aside.

To assemble
On a warm corn tortilla, add some scrambled eggs, chopped bacon and salsa. Enjoy!

5 instagram settings you need to turn ON 🔥

🌼 First, set up a professional account

1️⃣ Suggested accounts - This is so important and game changer!

☑ Log on to Instagram on your laptop or desktop
☑ Go to your profile and click on “Edit profile”
☑ Scroll down and turn on “Show account suggestions" on profiles.

➪ This will make your profile more discoverable when someone follows a similar profile to yours.

2️⃣ Suggested content

☑ Go to “Settings" > click on "Suggested content”
☑ Choose specific words and phrases for content you DO NOT want to see

➪ Whenever you see content in your feed that doesn't relate to your niche, add keywords to it

3️⃣ Train your Algorithm (Content for your niche)

☑  Go to the Explore page
☑  Choose posts and reels relevant to your niche. Click on the 3 dots and select "Interested".

➪ Using this method, you are letting IG know what type of content you post and increase your visibility.

4️⃣ High-Quality Video

☑ Go to “Settings and Privacy”
☑ Select “Media quality” in the “Your app and media” section.
☑ Turn on “Upload at highest quality”.

➪ High-quality videos on Instagram Reels are crucial for grabbing attention, appearing professional, and standing out!

5️⃣ Refresh your search history

☑ Tap your profile icon
☑ Tap the Menu = "Hamburger" icon (three horizontal lines)
☑ Tap "Your activity"
☑ Tap "Recent searches"
☑ Hit "Clear all"

➪ Stop confusing your algorithm by doing this since Algo works based on the info we provide.

☑ Go into your setting
☑ Go to "Account Status" to make sure you have all green check marks

The story of the most resilient doggies I’ve ever met:

We stumbled upon this little guy and a handful of other dogs inhabiting a remote mountain village sitting at 4,500 meters above sea level along the Huayhuash trek in the Peruvian Andes.

These dogs live in the purest form of nature, freely exploring these vast mountains day in and day out. But at night, they need to endure the unforgiving climate, sleeping outdoors in temperatures plummeting to -15 degrees. When we woke up from our tent in the morning, we found the dogs covered from head to toe in frost and ice. Which happens every night as they sleep on the frozen grass.

If we had known they sleep outside next to the tents, then a massive snuggle party with the 10 dogs living around the village would have been in order. 

When you travel around lower income countries you run into SO many dogs that you wish you could just take with you.

Should I go back and steal him?
